# ConvertIA — DEV / CI-TOOLING environment (NOT application runtime config).
#
# ConvertIA the APP is fully offline and reads NO environment at runtime
# (SSOT Principle 4 — zero egress, no phone-home, no telemetry). This file
# documents only the secrets/config the BUILD + GATE tooling uses locally, so a
# contributor can work inside the project without reaching out to a global
# credential store.
#
# Usage: copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# NEVER commit `.env` — it is gitignored on purpose. Only this template is tracked.

# --- GitHub access (gate-tool pin fetching, repo-config assertions, CI prep) ---
# Used by the gate/release tooling for: fetching public release checksums +
# pinned-action commit SHAs, and the P0.2.8 branch-protection / required-status
# assertions. `gh` and most scripts honour GH_TOKEN.
#
# Least-privilege recommendation — a FINE-GRAINED PAT scoped to Ne-IA/convertia:
#   Contents: read/write · Administration: read/write · Workflows: read/write · Metadata: read
# (a broad classic `repo` + `admin:org` token also works but grants far more than needed).
GH_TOKEN=
GITHUB_REPOSITORY=Ne-IA/convertia

# --- Release signing (P10 ONLY — not needed before the release pipeline) ---
# At release time these live as GitHub Actions repository SECRETS, not in local dev.
# Listed here only so the full credential surface is documented in one place.
# MINISIGN_SECRET_KEY=
# MINISIGN_PASSWORD=
